<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-01-04T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-01-04T20:00:00-05:00" n="416" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d416">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.01/30: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Robbins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-04T19:00:00-06:00">January 4, 1931—7
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>3. Department’s telegram January 3, 3 p.m. Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            informs me Government of Salvador takes attitude suggested by the
                            Department and is extending recognition to Reina Andrade as Provisional
                            President.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Robbins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>